records.addlTxt:
Defendant Michael M Fant in court with attorney Scott F. Anderson.  Danielle E. Chojnacki appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 18 MONTHS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 9 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 12 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 6 MONTHS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS with the following conditions:

1) Court ordered 6 months of condition time in the House of Correction, 
    CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence, release for the Day Reporting 
    Center ONLY, with good time credit, with credit for 0 DAYS time served. 
    Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. 
2) Maintain absolute sobriety.  Defendant NOT possess or
     use any controlled substances unless by valid prescription; 
3) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
4) Attend at least 1 sobriety support group per week. 
5) No firearms; weapons;
6) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
7) No contact with Arthur G. Jr. (3-9-91), or Earl J. (10-30-71);
8) Attend and successfully complete a Parenting class.
9) Seek/maintain full time employment;
10) Pay all mandatory costs and surcharges during the course 
      of probation to the probation agent, cash bail to apply. 
      Any remaining balance at the end of probation will be
      due immediately or an entry of an entry of a civil judgment. 
11) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 


Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  
Firearm possession; and Voting 
